For reference what I did to get this running.
This is not hard to perform but hard to figure out what needs to be in place for it to work.

```bash
# The target name I want
IMAGENAME=demo
TAG=latest
cd my-webhosting-dir

# Copy to temporary directory
skopeo copy docker-daemon:something:latest dir:/tmp/something

# Create target tree
mkdir -p v2/${IMAGENAME}/{manifests,blobs}

# Handle manifest of the tag
mv /tmp/something/manifest.json v2/${IMAGENAME}/manifests/${TAG}
( cd v2/${IMAGENAME}/manifests/ && cp ${TAG} sha256:$(sha256sum ${TAG} | cut -d' ' -f1) )

# Not needed
rm /tmp/something/version

# At this point only the blobs are left in the output dir
# Copy and rename all the blobs
( cd /tmp/something && ls *) | while read blobname ; do mv /tmp/something/${blobname} v2/${IMAGENAME}/blobs/sha256:${blobname} ; done
```

And add this to my httpd (in this case a fragment for nginx)
```
    location /v2/demo/manifests/ {
        add_header    Docker-Distribution-API-Version 'registry/2.0';
        default_type  'application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.v2+json';
    }
    location /v2/demo/blobs/ {
        add_header    Docker-Distribution-API-Version 'registry/2.0';
        default_type  'application/octet-stream';
    }

```

From there I can do `docker pull hostname/demo:latest`
